column18: Would you rather drive or be driven by a self-driving autonomous car?
column19: Do you feel safe being driven by a self-driving autonomous car? 1 is not safe at all and 10 being very safe. Use your imagination as fully self-driving autonomous cars are not available on the market right now.
column20: What level of automation in cars would you be interested in if you plan to buy one?
column21: When you think about buying a car (up to 5 years from now) how likely are you to consider purchasing a partially self-driving car?
column22: When you think about buying a car (up to 10 years from now) how likely are you to consider purchasing a fully self-driving car?
column23: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Is safer than non-self-driving cars
column24: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Lower insurance costs
column25: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Allows multi-tasking while car drives
column26: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Highest safety ratings given by government agencies
column27: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Switches to self-driving mode on highways
column28: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Switches to self-driving mode in traffic
column29: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Offers better mileage and lower maintenance than non-self-driving cars
column30: For which of the following reasons do you think you are (very likely/likely/neutral) to purchase a partially/fully self-driving autonomous car? Rank your reasons by using drag and drop. - Drops me off, finds a parking spot and parks on it own
column31: Fully automated cars are expected to cost $5000-9000 more on top of a regular car price for all new features. Would you be willing to spend more? If yes, how much?
column32: For which new features would you be willing to pay more? Rank the features by using drag and drop. - Safety Features
column33: For which new features would you be willing to pay more? Rank the features by using drag and drop. - Connectivity Features
column34: For which new features would you be willing to pay more? Rank the features by using drag and drop. - Full/partial self-drive
column35: For which new features would you be willing to pay more? Rank the features by using drag and drop. - Alternative engine
column36: What is your opinion on self-driving cars?
column37: Which factors would build your trust with driving in fully self-driving cars? Rank the factors by using drag and drop. - Car is offered by a well-known brand you trust
column38: Which factors would build your trust with driving in fully self-driving cars? Rank the factors by using drag and drop. - An established track record of self-driving cars used on the roads safely
column39: Which factors would build your trust with driving in fully self-driving cars? Rank the factors by using drag and drop. - Government regulations/approval of self-driving cars
column40: Which factors would build your trust with driving in fully self-driving cars? Rank the factors by using drag and drop. - A friend or family member using a self-driving car
column41: How concerned are you with regards to the legal liability of drivers/owners of self-driving cars?
column42: Do you consider autonomous driving as a useful advancement?
